tip.text: Salpicao was very tender and tasty. Fabada was flavorful. Tuna salpicao was ok. Don't think it's worth the P450 though. Rice is served in a fun donut shape.
Order coffee after your meal. They bake their own cupcakes and grind their own coffee beans! Freshly ground Italian roast.

Servings are huge! 2 of us split the seafood rice and tuna kimbap. Rice had TOO much onion and squid was tough but other than that, it was good. Can't eat the kimbap with poise as they're HUGE. Sulit!
Quick service. The mais con yelo was strange. It was more like a corn shake than anything. I'm missing the crushed ice.
Cookie dough skillet was tooth-achingly sweet. Black coffee is necessary. Can be shared by 4 people.
